        "desc": "A provincial park rich with Canadian history, located on the Mattawa River fur trade route used by Samuel de Champlain in 1615. The park sits 14 km west of Mattawa where the Mattawa and Amable-du-Fond Rivers meet. The Voyageur Heritage Centre features interactive exhibits on the fur trade and Indigenous history. Paddlers can try the famous Voyageur Canoe Tours on a 10m replica fur trade canoe in July and August. Four hiking trails from easy to challenging, swimming beaches, wildlife viewing, and full-service camping. 48,000+ visitors annually. Named a Canadian Heritage River.",
